509:     /// Leave the address acquired for now, but free it when the next checkpoint becomes durable.
510:     /// This ensures that it will not be overwritten during the current checkpoint — the block may
511:     /// still be needed if we crash and recover from the current checkpoint.
512:     /// (TODO) If the block was created since the last checkpoint then it's safe to free
